<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-770-990  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 770 990.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  August 13 1990 v7 n31 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SCSI bus repeater can provide 6-meter connections. (small computersystem interface) (Applied Concepts Inc.'s ACI 1074 SCSI Plus BusRepeater) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Applied Concepts Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Applied Concepts ACI 1074 SCSI Plus Bus Repeater (Computercommunications equipment) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Small Computer Systems InterfaceBusesProduct IntroductionRepeaters.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SCSI bus repeater can provide 6-meter connectionsandM;SAN DIEGO -- Applied Concepts has introduced a SCSI bus repeater that allowsusers to extend host-to-peripheral connections to as far as 6 meters.andM;The repeater is transparent to users and can sustain data transfer rates ofup to 5MB per second over a 6-meter segment, according to Applied Conceptsofficials.andM;The ACI 1074 SCSI Plus Bus Repeater links directly to standard SCSI interfacehost adapters, according to Richard Rauch, Applied Concepts' president.andM;&quot;It's kind of like an extension cord.andP;  We rebuffer everything to repeat thesignal.andP;  It's purely a repeater for the bus, connecting parallel cable toparallel cable,&quot; Rauch said.andM;The SCSI Plus Bus Repeater conforms to ANSI X3.131 specifications andprovides single-end device termination for SCSI and SCSI II buses, accordingto Rauch.andM;The repeater includes a wall-unit power adapter.andM;SCSI Plus Bus Repeater units can be daisy-chained, although some performancedegradation occurs once connections extend to 6 meters, according to Rauch.andM;The performance degradation is caused by SCSI specifications, Rauch said.andM;&quot;I couldn't see anyone wanting to use more than three or four of thesethings.andP;  After a certain point, you'd want to switch to a product like ourfiber-optic SCSI extension,&quot; he said.andM;The Laser Link Two fiber-optic extension, introduced earlier this year, addsas much as 3,000 feet to SCSI connections, according to Rauch.andM;&quot;A product linke the SCSI Plus Bus Repeater is susceptible to environmentalinterference.andP;  The fiber extension is not,&quot; he said.andM;Laser Link Two consists of a pair interfaces that converts parallel signalsto serial for transmission over fiber-optic cable, then reconvert the signalto parallel, according to a company spokeswoman.andM;The ACI 1074 SCSI Plus Bus Repeater is available now and is priced at $350.andO;The Laser Link Two fiber-optic link is also available and is priced at $950per node.andM;Applied Concepts Inc. can be contacted at 5350-H, Eastgate Mall, San Diego,CA 92121, (619) 453-0090.andO;</TEXT></DOC>